fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.data

Interface IDataStructure

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<IData>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IArrayItem, IItem

    public interface IDataStructure
extends Iterable<IData>
    Defines the basic API for a fixed or dynamic record prototype that contains data values.

    Data structures can be used directly in for-each constructs, to iterate over data elements.

    Thread safety: implementations are required to be safe for concurrent read/write access.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies

      • getExtraCells

        SortedSet<ICell> getExtraCells()
        Gets extra cells, without duplicate definitions. This contains both optional cells (non mandatory cells, known in advance) and dynamic cells (non mandatory, not known in advance, such as arbitrary property fields from a schemaless database).
        Returns:
        a collection of cells, possibly empty, never null.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:

      • addCell

        IData addCell(ICell cell)
       throws StructureException
        Adds a dynamic cell to this data structure, if this operation is supported.
        Parameters:
        cell - the non-null cell to add.
        Returns:
        a data object, to set the value for the cell.
        Throws:
        StructureException - if the specified cell is null, or if it cannot be associated with this data structure, or if it is already associated. In particular, you should not attempt to add any fixed cells. Always thrown by data structures that do not support dynamic cells.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        removeCell(ICell), getExtraCells(), ICellStructure.getOptionalCells()

      • removeCell

        void removeCell(ICell cell)
         throws StructureException
        Removes a dynamic cell from this data structure, if this operation is supported. Does nothing if the cell was previously associated and already removed.
        Parameters:
        cell - the non-null cell to remove.
        Throws:
        StructureException - if the specified cell is null, or if it cannot be removed from this data structure. In particular, you should not attempt to remove fixed cells. Always thrown by data structures that do not support dynamic cells.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        addCell(ICell), getExtraCells(), ICellStructure.getOptionalCells()
